OL,3,CUK supermarkets warn business rates
OL,4,Crise could push up food inflation
OL,6,FIt reads: "If the industry faces
OL,7,Fhigher taxes in the coming Budget `
OL,8,Fsuch as being included in the new
OL,9,Fsurtax on business rates ` our ability
OL,10,Fto deliver value for our customers
OL,11,Fwill become even more challenging and
OL,12,Fit will be households who inevitably
OL,13,Ffeel the impact.
OL,15,F"Given the costs currently falling on
OL,16,Fthe industry, including from the last
OL,17,Fbudget, high food inflation is likely
OL,18,Fto persist into 2026.
